    "The distribution of question types and subjects within the whole set and mock examination set of questions is summarised in Table 1 and S1 Table alongside performance.",
    "GPT-4 represents a significant advance on GPT-3.5 in ophthalmological knowledge and reasoning.",
    "Overall performance over 347 questions was significantly higher for GPT-4 (61.7%) than GPT-3.5 (48.41%; χ 2 = 12.32, p<0.01), with results detailed in S1 Fig and S1 Table.",
    "ChatGPT performance was consistent across question types and subjects (S1 Table).",
    "For GPT-4, no significant variation was observed with respect to first order and higher order questions (χ 2 = 0.22, p = 0.64), or subjects defined by the Royal College of Ophthalmologists (Fisher's exact test over 2000 iterations, p = 0.23)."
